- Build a Three-Tier AWS Network VPC from Scratch
- Create Internet Gateway and associated it to the vpc
- Create 2 public subnets for webserver, 2 private subnets for appserver, 2 private subnets for dataserver. 
- Create 1 public route table and 1 private route table. public subnets will be associated to public RT. private subnets will be associated to private RT
- Create Nat Gateways on public subnets and associated then to private appservers.
- Create the Security Groups: alb-security-group, webserver-security-group, appserver-security-group,databaseserver-security-group
- Create the RDS Instance
- Create the Elastic File System (EFS)
- Install WordPress
- Create an Application Load Balancer
- Register a New Domain Name in Route 53
- Create a Record Set in Route 53
- Register for an SSL Certificate in AWS Certificate Manager
- SSH into Instance in the Private Subnet
- Create an HTTPS Listener for the Application Load Balancer
- Create an Auto Scaling Group
- Install WordPress Theme and Template